        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 5:41PM PDT by NWS Sacramento CA</headline>
        <description>At 541 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles west of Ono, or 12 miles northeast of Yolla Bolly District Rs,
moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ono.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
